        <h2>> <a href="http://ez.no/About-eZ/Blog/Content-Is-Gold" title="Content Is Gold">Content Is Gold</a></h2>
     </div>

    <div class="attribute-byline">
	    </div>

    

    <div class="attribute-body float-break">
      <p><i>(If you missed the blog on the Future Direction of eZ,&nbsp;<a href="http://ez.no/About-eZ/Blog/The-Future-Direction-of-eZ" target="_self">read all about it here.</a>)</i></p><p>In a world where relatively “newborn” digital companies are turning industries upside down, the media industry is an obvious example: traditional, print-based media groups are struggling to digitize their business models while facing the challenge of new companies that were not there ten years ago.</p><p>As the most used content management platform in the media industry, we are working closely both with new pure digital media companies as well as with these traditional media groups.</p><p>While the media is discussing “digital first” or “mobile first” and other strategies to lead this transformation, we see the same trend in just about any vertical. New customer habits combined with new players make traditional business methods more challenging, while simultaneously creating huge opportunities for those who recognize and embrace them. Retail, travel and financial services are examples of the industries affected.</p><p>Thus, I believe that in the digital economy of the future, every company in any vertical is a publisher and needs to think like a media company - and content is the key driver of their success.</p><a name="eztoc391251_1" id="eztoc391251_1"></a><h2>Why?</h2><p>With changing customer habits, the buying process is moving into the digital realm. The right content about your product or services, from the right source, available through the right channel, is key to obtaining a buying decision.</p><p>So what can we learn from the media industry? For any successful digital business, you need to ensure:</p><p>#1:&nbsp;That you can involve any person, within your company or outside, in your publishing process in a simple, social, but controlled way.</p><div class="separator"><span></span></div><p>#2:&nbsp;That you can utilize the power of all types of content - be it text, film or pictures - from any source, such as your ERP, Document Management or CRM.</p><div class="separator"><span></span></div><p>#3:&nbsp;That you can publish your content in any of today’s channels - mobile, web, print, tablet, social - and more importantly, the channels of the future.</p><div class="separator"><span></span></div><p>
Content is Gold, and is the basis of any successful digital business model, today and in the future.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
At eZ we will not forget this, even while everybody runs after the next hyped trend. eZ will continue to focus on creating great content management software, making sure anyone can create any type of content and publish it in any channel - of today and in the future - and providing tools to optimize this content lifecycle.<br />
&nbsp;<br />Just as in your digital business, we treat Content as Gold, and create the tools to help new, fully digital and traditional businesses remain successful, for today and tomorrow.</p>
    </div>

